Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting
#lid.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once
boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered)
and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice
will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Halve and
peel the @Onion{1}. Chop both into 2cm chunks.

Drain the @Firm Tofu{280%g} and cut into 2cm cubes. Pat dry with #kitchen paper{}.

Put the @Cornflour{20%g} into a #medium bowl{}, then season with @ground black pepper{} and add half the
@Chinese Five Spice{1%sachet}. Mix together, then add the tofu and toss to coat
evenly.

Heat the @Oil{2%tbsp} in a #large frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the tofu to the #frying pan{}. Fry until slightly crispy,
~{8-10%minutes}. Turn frequently to ensure it doesn't burn.

While the tofu fries, discard any excess cornflour and wipe out the #bowl{}.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Crush the
@Salted Peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

When cooked, transfer the tofu to a #plate{} lined with kitchen paper. Wipe out
your pan, then pop back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the pepper and onion. Stir-fry until golden and slightly charred,
~{5-7%minutes}. Season with pepper.

Meanwhile, in the (now empty) medium bowl, mix together the
@Soy Sauce{25%ml}, garlic, @Honey{30%g}, @Sriracha Sauce{15%g} and remaining
Chinese Five Spice with the @Tomato Ketchup{4%tbsp} and @Water{100%ml} for the
sauce.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Add the fried tofu back into the frying pan with the veg and stir in the sticky
sauce. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Once thickened, remove from the heat, then taste and add more salt, pepper and
a pinch of @?sugar{pinch}(if you have any) if needed.

Add a splash of @?water{} if it's a bit too thick.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the sticky tofu and veg, spooning over the remaining sauce from the pan.

Finish by sprinkling over the peanuts. Enjoy!